## Install

```powershell
Install-PSResource {{ModuleName}}   # from the PowerShell Gallery (once published)
```

## How to ship a change

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    Edit["Edit a function in Public/"] --> Test["Run Pester tests locally"]
    Test --> Commit["Conventional commit + push"]
    Commit --> CI["CI: PSScriptAnalyzer + Pester"]
    CI -->|green| Merge["Merge to main"]
    Merge --> RP["release-please opens a release PR<br/>(bumps ModuleVersion in the .psd1)"]
    RP -->|you approve| Tag["Tag + GitHub release"]
    Tag --> Pub["Publish-PSResource to PSGallery<br/>(gated approval — you click go)"]
```

## Layout

- `Public/` — exported functions (one per file; the file's base name is the function name).
- `Private/` — internal helpers (not exported).
- `Tests/` — Pester tests.
- `{{ModuleName}}.psd1` — the module manifest; `{{ModuleName}}.psm1` dot-sources `Public/` + `Private/`.

See [`AGENTS.md`](AGENTS.md) for the START-HERE map. Follows the
[RepoKit](https://github.com/PBNZ/repo-kit) standard.
